<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>RASH case sheet part</title>
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css" id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet"
      title="dark">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="derma infectious General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: RASH</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Site &amp; Distribution</span>
          <ul>
            <li>LOCALIZED
              <ul>
                <li class="infectious">Fungal (Tinea)</li>
                <li class="derma">Contact Dermatitis</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>GENERALIZED (Widespread)
              <ul>
                <li class="infectious">Viral Exanthem (See specific patterns
                  below)</li>
                <li class="rheumatic">Drug Eruption</li>
                <li class="derma">Eczema Flare</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>SPECIFIC DISTRIBUTION PATTERNS
              <ul>
                <li class="derma">Flexures (bends of elbows/knees):
                  <ul>
                    <li>Atopic Dermatitis (Eczema)</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="derma">Extensors (outside of elbows/knees):
                  <ul>
                    <li>Psoriasis</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="cns">Dermatomal (one nerve strip):
                  <ul>
                    <li>Shingles (Herpes Zoster)</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="infectious">Face first, then down body
                  (Cephalocaudal):
                  <ul>
                    <li>Measles, Rubella</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="infectious">Trunk first, then out:
                  <ul>
                    <li>Roseola, Varicella</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="infectious">"Slapped Cheeks":
                  <ul>
                    <li>Fifth Disease</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="infectious">Hands, Feet, and Mouth: HFMD</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Where did the rash start, and where has it
          spread?"</span></div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>:
            Onset</span>
          <ul>
            <li>ACUTE (Minutes-Hours):
              <ul>
                <li class="rheumatic emergency">Urticaria</li>
                <li class="derma">Contact Dermatitis</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>SUBACUTE (Days):
              <ul>
                <li class="infectious">Viral Exanthems</li>
                <li class="rheumatic">Drug Reactions</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>CHRONIC (Weeks-Months):
              <ul>
                <li class="derma rheumatic">Eczema, Psoriasis</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When did it appear? Suddenly over minutes, or
          gradually over days?"</span></div>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>:
            Duration</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How long do individual spots last? Do they come
          and go, or stay put?"</span></div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
            Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="grey">Allergies - Paracetamol? <span class="warning">Ibuprofen</span>?
              steroids? any recent antibiotics.</li>
            <li class="grey">New foods, medications, soaps?</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does anything make it better or worse?"</span></div>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
            Character (Morphology)</span>
          <ul>
            <li>MORPHOLOGY
              <ul>
                <li>Maculopapular (red bumps/spots):
                  <ul>
                    <li class="infectious">Measles, Rubella, Roseola</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Vesicular (blisters):
                  <ul>
                    <li class="infectious">Varicella, HFMD, Shingles</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Pustular (pus-filled):
                  <ul>
                    <li class="infectious derma">Folliculitis, Acne</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Wheals (hives):
                  <ul>
                    <li class="rheumatic">Urticaria</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Lacy/Reticular:
                  <ul>
                    <li class="infectious">Fifth Disease</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Sandpaper-like:
                  <ul>
                    <li class="infectious git">Scarlet Fever</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"What do the spots look like? Flat, bumpy,
          blisters? Are they itchy?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Radiation (Spread Pattern) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Radiation (Spread)</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"We've covered the spread, thank you."</span></div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms (with VIRAL EXANTHEM SUB-MODULE) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
            Associated Symptoms</span>
          <ul>
            <li>GENERAL
              <ul>
                <li class="rheumatic">Joint Pain </li>
                <ul>
                  <li class="rheumatic">HSP, </li>
                  <li class="rheumatic">Viral Arthritis</li>
                  <li class="rheumatic">Lyme disease</li>
                </ul>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>DEHYDRATION </strong>&ndash; dry nappies, lethargy,
              sunken eyes.</li>
            <li><strong>FEVER PROFILE</strong> &ndash;
              <ul>
                <li>peak temp, </li>
                <li>timing in relation to rash, </li>
                <li>response to paracetamol; </li>
                <li>high fever <strong>preceding</strong> rash that then falls
                  ( ↘︎ ) suggests <span class="infectious">Roseola</span>.</li>
                <li>Lyme Disease</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="infectious">CLUES FOR VIRAL EXANTHEMS
              <ul>
                <li><b>Fever Timing:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>High fever first, THEN rash appears as fever breaks?
                      -&gt; <b class="infectious">Roseola</b></li>
                    <li>Fever and rash at the same time? -&gt; <b class="infectious">Measles,
                        Rubella, Varicella</b></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><b>Prodrome (Symptoms BEFORE rash):</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Cough, Coryza (runny nose), Conjunctivitis (3 C's)?
                      -&gt; <b class="infectious">Measles</b></li>
                    <li>Sore throat? -&gt; <b class="infectious git">Scarlet
                        Fever</b></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><b>Mouth / Mucosal Signs:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Koplik spots (white spots in cheeks)? -&gt; <b class="infectious">Measles</b></li>
                    <li>Mouth ulcers? -&gt; <b class="infectious">HFMD /
                        Herpangina</b></li>
                    <li>Strawberry tongue? -&gt; <b class="infectious git">Scarlet
                        Fever / Kawasaki</b></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><b>Other Key Signs:</b>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Swollen nodes behind ears? -&gt; <b class="infectious">Rubella</b></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b><u>PRURITUS </u></b>(ITCH): <span class="infectious derma">Scabies,
                Eczema, Varicella</span> are intensely itchy.</li>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>SEVERITY <br>
                </strong></li>
              <li><strong></strong><span style="color: #09a8cc;">A/R </span>;
                ask about scratching, calamine, antihistamine, short nails,
                emollient baths.</li>
            </ul>
            <li><em>PAIN</em>: <span class="cns">Shingles</span> is classically
              painful.</li>
            <li>Glands</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Lyme Disease</li>
              <li>Kawasaki</li>
              <li><br>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <li>Joint pains</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Auto immune diseses for psorasis</li>
              <li>other auto immune disesse</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Any other symptoms like fever, cough, joint pain,
          or mouth sores?"</span></div>
      <!-- M: Medical / Medication Background -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>M</strong>:
            Medical / Medication Background</span>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Past Medical History</strong> &ndash; eczema, asthma,
              immunosuppression, prematurity.</li>
            <li><strong>Drug Allergies</strong> &ndash; especially antibiotics.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does your child have any other health problems or
          regular medicines? Any allergies?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Progression</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Multiple stages at once (spots, blisters, crusts)? &rarr; <span
                class="infectious">Varicella</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How have the spots changed over time since they
          first appeared?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Pattern & People -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Pattern &amp; People</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="infectious">SICK CONTACTS (school, nursery, home)</li>
            <li class="General">IMMUNISATION STATUS (MMR, <strong>Varicella</strong>)</li>
            <li><strong>HIGH‑RISK CONTACTS</strong> &ndash; pregnant household
              members, newborns, immunocompromised relatives (require separate
              advice).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is anyone else sick? Any recent travel? Are
          immunisations up to date?"</span></div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>:
            Effect on Life</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Appears generally well -&gt; <b class="infectious">Roseola,
                Fifth Disease</b></li>
            <li>Appears miserable/very unwell -&gt; <b class="infectious">Measles</b></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How is your child's overall energy? Are they
          playful, or very sick?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Red Flags</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="warning">Dangerours Diseases</li>
            <li class="warning">Complications of suspected Diseases - ABCDE</li>
            <li class="emergency infectious">Neck stiffness, NON-BLANCHING RASH
              (Petechiae/Purpura) + FEVER -&gt; <b class="emergency">Meningococcemia</b></li>
            <li class="emergency infectious">RASH (maculopapular) + FEVER -&gt;
              <b>Measles</b></li>
            <ul>
              <li class="emergency infectious"><b>A - <br>
                </b></li>
              <li class="emergency infectious"><b>B - Pnumonia</b></li>
              <li class="emergency infectious"><b>Ear infections<br>
                </b></li>
            </ul>
            <li class="emergency rheumatic">HIVES + Swelling/Difficulty
              Breathing -&gt; <b class="emergency">Anaphylaxis</b></li>
            <li class="emergency derma">BLISTERING/PEELING with mucosal
              involvement -&gt; <b class="emergency">SJS/TEN</b></li>
            <li class="infectious cvs rheumatic emergency">FEVER &gt; 5 days +
              Redness (eyes, mouth) + Swelling (hands/feet) -&gt; <b class="emergency">Kawasaki
                Disease</b></li>
            <li class="warning">Rash <strong>red, hot or painful</strong> (2`
              bacterial infection).</li>
            <li class="warning">Ataxia / unsteady gait (possible varicella
              cerebellitis).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"I must ask some specific questions. Does the rash
          not fade with pressure? Any trouble breathing?"</span></div>
      <!-- S: Severity -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Severity / Scale</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how itchy or bothersome is
          the rash?"</span></div>
      <!-- Parent / Carer Risk Discussion -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>Parent /
              Carer Exposure</strong></span>
          <ul>
            <li>If <em>non‑immune</em> and exposure within 24 h &rarr; discuss
              adult vaccination or prophylactic aciclovir.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Have you ever had chicken pox or been vaccinated?
          Are you or anyone at home pregnant, on cancer treatment, or taking
          medicines that weaken immunity?"</span></div>
    </div>
    <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height_mothership.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height.js"></script>
    <script src="double_click_collapse_details.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
